content:
Enable Listen In for Supervisors

This feature is available with these telephony models:

SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

To let Amazon Connect users listen in to a voice call, assign the ManagerListenIn permission in Amazon Connect.
From Amazon Connect, go to Manage users, and then Security profiles.
Reuse an existing security profile or create another one to add Listen In capabilities.
Enable the ManagerListenIn user permission.
Turn on Enable Multi-Party Calls and Enhanced Monitoring. 
Assign the security profile to users with the Contact Center Supervisor permission set assigned to them.
title: Enable Listen In for Supervisors in Service Cloud
